    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Does the scan hurt?",
        "answer": " No. MRI is painless; you only hear tapping sounds.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I wear my bra during the MRI Dorsal Spine?",
        "answer": "Under-wired bras must be removed; we provide a gown.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon can I get an appointment?",
        "answer": "We offer same-day or next-day slots; book via website or call"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is gadolinium dye safe for kidneys?",
        "answer": "We screen creatinine levels; low-dose, macrocyclic agents minimise risk.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Will my insurance cover the test?",
        "answer": "Most panels empanel Cadabams Diagnostics; cashless facility available.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I am claustrophobic about the MRI scanner?",
        "answer": "  If you suffer from claustrophobia or anxiety about enclosed spaces, please inform our staff at Cadabams Diagnostics when you book your **MRI Dorsal Spine** appointment. We can discuss several options to help you manage this:\n        *   Our technologists are experienced in supporting anxious patients and can talk you through the procedure.\n        *   You can often listen to music through headphones.\n        *   An eye mask might help.\n        *   In some cases, your referring doctor may prescribe a mild sedative to take before the scan. If sedation is used, you will need someone to drive you home.\n        *   For very severe cases, your doctor might discuss alternatives, though standard closed MRI provides the best image quality."
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does an MRI for the thoracic spine cost?",
        "answer": "The **cost of MRI for thoracic spine** (or MRI Dorsal Spine) can vary depending on several factors, including whether contrast material is used and the complexity of the scan. For specific and up-to-date pricing information for an **MRI Dorsal Spine** at Cadabams Diagnostics, please contact our billing department directly."
      }
